parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to inconvenient and potentially hazardous situations.
symptoms: The ignition switch freezes in the start position
making it difficult to start the vehicle
the vehicle will not start
the ignition switch fails
all electrical features become inoperable
including headlights
radio
and power windows.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel System Defect Leading to Engine Fires
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A defect in the fuel system can cause engine fires, which can lead to serious accidents, injuries, or even fatalities.
symptoms: Raw gasoline smell when starting the vehicle
fuel leaks in the engine compartment
engine compartment fires
spontaneous fires in the engine compartment while the vehicle is parked.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling of the engine without warning can cause a loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls without warning while driving at highway speeds
the engine shuts off unexpectedly
the vehicle loses power and comes to a stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Timing Belt, Pulley, and Tensioner Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing belt, pulley, and tensioner can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs and potentially leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The timing belt breaks or fails
the pulley and tensioner fail
the engine makes unusual noises or vibrations
the engine loses power or stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the catalytic converter can cause engine damage, reduce vehicle performance, and lead to costly repairs.
symptoms: A rattling or rasping sound comes from the exhaust system
the catalytic converter becomes clogged
the engine runs rough or misfires
the vehicle's performance is reduced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause fluid leaks, leading to premature wear on transmission components, reduced performance, and potential complete transmission failure, which can result in loss of vehicle control and accidents.
symptoms: Transmission fluid leaks
unusual noises or vibrations from the transmission
difficulty shifting gears
slipping or hesitation between gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the CV boot can cause the CV joint to wear prematurely, leading to vibration, noise, and potentially causing the driveshaft to fail, which can result in loss of vehicle control and accidents.
symptoms: Vibrations or noise from the CV joint
clicking or clunking sounds when turning
uneven tire wear.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Downshifting Issues on Wet Roads
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended downshifting on wet roads can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents or near-miss incidents.
symptoms: Transmission downshifts unexpectedly on wet roads
feeling like pressing the brake pedal
loss of vehicle control.
